title: Toasty Waffles Training Road Race Series
Tour of Kansas City
description: One day of sprint racing and two days of criterium racing.  Preregistration is recommended.
course:
Sprint Series, Friday, June 20th, New Longview, Lee's Summit, MO. ~200 meter sprint course.

Criterium Series, New Longview, Lee's Summit, MO, Saturday, June 21. Course length: 1.33 miles.


Criterium Series, Cliff Drive, Kansas City, MO, Sunday, June 22.  Course length: 2.9 miles.
registration:
Regular online registration goes through 6/13/2014. Late online registration is 6/14/2014 through 6/18/2014.

For those registering same day, onsite registration opens one hour before the first event and closes for each category 15 minutes before the race time indicated on the schedule below.
directions: Course maps, directions, parking, and other details can be found online at TourOfKC.com

title: Ballwin Cycles Dirt Crits @ Valley Park
Joe Becker Memorial Scratch Race State Championship
Kansas City Cyclocross Clinic
description:
8am   Bike check in, Free Coffee, Bike Tuneups.
8:30am  Bicycle Equipment Clinic
9am  Bicycle Fit Clinic
9:30am We ride!  
10am  Nutrition and Training
10:30am  How the cyclocross race works, and starting fast!
10:45am Off camber turns, super turns, doing them fast and how to know when to use your brakes.
11:00am Barriers. How to be smooth, fast, and efficient getting on and off your bike.
11:30am.  We race!
12 noon.  Free lunch.  Beer.   Open time for all the questions.
directions: Location is at the Volker Bicycles on 1717 W 39th in Kansas City, MO.  Using I35, take the 7th st exit heading south on 7th st to 39th.  Go left(east)  on 39th across the state line, park after you see Bell St.  Parking in the Chipotle/starbucks parking lot is probably best.
